pgsql_dump_to_cockroachdb_variations

- when encountered a PK definition, better put it in the table's creation statement.
- when encountered a 'foo ON CASCADE', better remove it.
- when encountered a 'USING btree' within an index creation statement, better remove it.
- when encountered a FK definition, better check if there is an index on targetted collumns, create it if there's not.
- when encountered something dealing with 'EXTENSION', better remove it
- when encountered a SEQUENCE starting from 1 and incrementing by 1, replace it by a SERIAL type.
	-> better remove the associate 'ALTER TABLE foo ALTER COLUMN bar SET DEFAULT nextval(...)'
	-> same for 'SELECT setval(xxx,n,b)